&lt;p data-olk-copy-source=&quot;MessageBody&quot;&gt;What’s it like to work at Kinder’s? Well, there’s a lot of snacking and geeking out over what we all cooked over the weekend. Beyond that, there’s also plenty of hard work. Because we don’t just like flavor, we’re obsessed with it.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With over 100 products sold nationwide, we’re now a top-five brand in multiple flavor categories at Costco, Walmart, Whole Foods, and more. We’re not your typical CPG company. Privately held and founder-led, we like to think of ourselves as a &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;pirate ship in a sea of cruise ships&lt;/span&gt;. Our crew is adventurous and fearless. We chart our own course and chase big ideas to make food unforgettable.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we expand globally and approach $1 billion in revenue, we need more smart-and-scrappy, flavor-obsessed people to come aboard. If you’re looking for a place where you can see the real impact of your work... &lt;strong&gt;this is it!&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Every day, you’ll be part of a journey to add flavor to millions of meals and lives.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;About the Role:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kinder’s is seeking an experienced and creatively driven Culinary Development Manager to join our team of passionate culinary professionals working hard to bring the future of flavor to consumers everywhere. This role is designed for a culinary leader who wants to grow inside an ambitious, fast-growing organization while representing Kinder’s through exceptional food execution and operational excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Culinary Development Manager will be a critical leader in contributing to our culinary development engine. This is a high-impact role responsible for supporting innovation cycles and driving culinary gold-standard formulation through the creation, testing, and refinement of new products and flavor profiles. This role blends hands-on cooking, product testing, recipe development, field execution, and cross-functional partnership. You will partner regularly with other functions such as Innovation, R&amp;amp;D, Product Development, Commercialization, Brand, Sales, and Operations, to ensure quality and facilitate the scale-up of new flavors.&lt;/p&gt;
